column3: GGames PlayedGames in which a player has appeared.GGames PlayedGames in which a player has appeared.
column4: ABAt BatsTrips to the plate that do not result in a walk, hit by pitch, sacrifice, or reach on interference.ABAt BatsTrips to the plate that do not result in a walk, hit by pitch, sacrifice, or reach on interference.
column5: RRunsWhen a baserunner safely reaches home plate and scores.RRunsWhen a baserunner safely reaches home plate and scores.
column6: HHitsWhen a batter reaches base safely on a fair ball unless the batter is deemed by the official scorer to have reached on an error or a fielder's choice.HHitsWhen a batter reaches base safely on a fair ball unless the batter is deemed by the official scorer to have reached on an error or a fielder's choice.
column7: 2BDoublesWhen a batter reaches on a hit and stops at second base or only advances farther than second base on an error or a fielder's attempt to put out another baserunner.2BDoublesWhen a batter reaches on a hit and stops at second base or only advances farther than second base on an error or a fielder's attempt to put out another baserunner.
column8: 3BTriplesWhen a batter reaches on a hit and stops at third base or only advances farther than third base on an error or a fielder's attempt to put out another baserunner.3BTriplesWhen a batter reaches on a hit and stops at third base or only advances farther than third base on an error or a fielder's attempt to put out another baserunner.
column9: HRHome RunsWhen a batter reaches on a hit, touches all bases, and scores a run without a putout recorded or the benefit of error.HRHome RunsWhen a batter reaches on a hit, touches all bases, and scores a run without a putout recorded or the benefit of error.
column10: caret-upcaret-downRBIRuns Batted InRuns which score because of the batter's safe hit, sac bunt, sac fly, infield out or fielder's choice or is forced to score by a bases loaded walk, hit batter, or interference.caret-upcaret-downRBIRuns Batted InRuns which score because of the batter's safe hit, sac bunt, sac fly, infield out or fielder's choice or is forced to score by a bases loaded walk, hit batter, or interference.
column11: BBWalksWhen a batter is awarded first base after four balls have been called by the umpire or the opposing team opts to intentionally award the batter first base.BBWalksWhen a batter is awarded first base after four balls have been called by the umpire or the opposing team opts to intentionally award the batter first base.
column12: SOStrikeoutsWhen the umpire calls three strikes on the batter.SOStrikeoutsWhen the umpire calls three strikes on the batter.
column13: SBStolen BasesWhen the runner advances one base unaided by a hit, a putout, an error, a force-out, a fielder's choice, a passed ball, a wild pitch, or a balk.SBStolen BasesWhen the runner advances one base unaided by a hit, a putout, an error, a force-out, a fielder's choice, a passed ball, a wild pitch, or a balk.
column14: CSCaught StealingWhen a runner attempts to steal but is tagged out before safely attaining the next base.CSCaught StealingWhen a runner attempts to steal but is tagged out before safely attaining the next base.
column15: AVGBatting AverageThe rate of hits per at bat.H/ABAVGBatting AverageThe rate of hits per at bat.H/AB
column16: OBPOn-Base PercentageThe rate at which a batter reached base in his plate appearances.(H+BB+HBP)/(AB+BB+HBP+SF)OBPOn-Base PercentageThe rate at which a batter reached base in his plate appearances.(H+BB+HBP)/(AB+BB+HBP+SF)
column17: SLGSlugging PercentageThe rate of total bases per at bat.(1B+2Bx2+3Bx3+HRx4)/ABSLGSlugging PercentageThe rate of total bases per at bat.(1B+2Bx2+3Bx3+HRx4)/AB
column18: OPSOn-Base Plus SluggingThe sum of on-base percentage and slugging percentage.OBP+SLGOPSOn-Base Plus SluggingThe sum of on-base percentage and slugging percentage.OBP+SLG
